  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n-\\Delta_T \\phi_n = \\lambda_n \\phi_n .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Frequency Relation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\omega_n^2 = \\lambda_n + m^2 .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $\\Omega\\subset M$ be a bounded region of the Trawinistic manifold.  \nBoundary conditions on $\\partial\\Omega$ force the Trawinistic Laplacian to admit eigenmodes:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n-\\Delta_T \\phi_n = \\lambda_n\\phi_n .\n\\end{equation}\n\nFor a massive field, the frequency of each mode satisfies the dispersion relation:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\omega_n^2=\\lambda_n+m^2 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThus confinement converts continuous spectral freedom into a discrete mode family.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nGeometry and boundary conditions discretize allowed field frequencies.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
